{
  "doc_id": "39504",
  "text": "Consequently, treatment with common vasoconstrictors after volume resuscitation does not reduce mortality or result in any differences in organ dysfunction. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] A new therapeutic option could be to interfere with pathways affecting the expression and action of vasoconstrictive receptors. Few studies have investigated downregulation of vasoconstrictive receptors as a cause of vasoplegia in patients with sepsis.",
